ost generous country]]''' by GNI 0.21%, Total aid: US$1.6 billion \n| || align=\"right\" |Economy||align=\"right\"|2013\t\n|<ref name=\"Global Humanitarian Assistance\" />\n|-\t\n|'''[[List of countries by refugee population|Biggest refugee hosting country]]''' with 3 million [[Refugees of the Syrian Civil War|Syrian]] and [[Refugees of Iraq|Iraqi refugees]] \n| || align=\"right\" |Demographics||align=\"right\"|2015\n|<ref name=\"unhcr.org\">{{cite web|url=http://www.unhcr.org/55016fff6.html|title=UNHCR warns of bleaker future for refugees as Syrian conflict enters 5th year|publisher=[[United Nations High Commissioner for Refugees]]|accessdate=2015-03-21}}</ref><ref name=\"Cihan News Agency\">{{cite news|url=http://www.cihan.com.tr/tr/haber/UN-agency-Turkey-biggest-refugee-hosting_7138-CHMTcwNzEzOC80|title=UN agency: Turkey biggest refugee-hosting country|date=17 March 2015|accessdate=21 March 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150402154427/http://www.cihan.com.tr/tr/haber/UN-agency-Turkey-biggest-refugee-hosting_7138-CHMTcwNzEzOC80|archivedate=2 April 2015|url-status=dead|publisher=[[Cihan News Agency]]}}</ref>\n|}\n\n===Tuvalu===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|- style=\"background:#ececec;\"\n! Statistic \n!Value!! Field !! Date\n!References\n|-\n|'''[[List of countries by immigrant population|Smallest number of immigrants]]''', 141\n| || align=\"right\" |Demographics||align=\"right\"|2015\n|\n|-\n|'''[[List of countries by GDP (nominal)|Lowest GDP (nominal)]]''', US$34 million\n| || align=\"right\" |Economy||align=\"right\"|2016\n|\n|-\n|'''[[List of countries by GDP (PPP)|Lowest GDP (PPP)]]''', US$41 million\n| || align=\"right\" |Economy||align=\"right\"|2017\n|\n|-\n|'''[[Land use statistics by country|Largest percentage of permanent crops]]''', 66.67%\n| || align=\"right\" |Agriculture<br />Geography ||align=\"right\"|2005\n|\n|-\n|'''[[List of countries by industrial production growth rate|Worst industrial production decline]]''',  -26.10% ([[