rs-promote-fair-trade-for-haitis-super-crop-2014-24|title=Perfumers promote fair trade for Haiti's 'super-crop'|editor=Adams, David|date=24 April 2014|website=Business Insider|accessdate=11 March 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n|{{flag|Honduras}}||'''[[List of countries by intentional homicide rate|Highest intentional homicide rate]]''', 103 per 100,000 people per year\n| || align=\"right\" |Demographics||align=\"right\"|2008\n|\n|-\n|{{flag|Hungary}}||'''Best performance at [[FINA Water Polo World Cup#Ranking|FINA Water Polo World Cup]] (men)''', 3 times winner (1979, 1995, 1999), 3 times runner-up (1993, 2002, 2006)\n| || align=\"right\" |Sports||align=\"right\"| 2009\n|\n|-\n|{{flag|Jamaica}}||'''[[Men's 100 metres world record progression|Fastest man]]''', [[Usain Bolt]], 12.42&nbsp;m/s\n| || align=\"right\" |Sports||align=\"right\"|2014\n|\n|-\n|{{flag|Jordan}}||'''[[List of countries by lowest point|Lowest depression below the sea level]]''', -428 m at [[Dead Sea]] (shared with [[Israel]] and [[State of Palestine]])\n| || align=\"right\" |Geography ||align=\"right\"|2012\n|\n|-\n|{{flag|Kuwait}}||'''[[List of countries by current account balance as a percentage of GDP|Highest current account balance as a percentage of GDP]]''', 35.35% \n| || align=\"right\" |Finance||align=\"right\"|2014\n|\n|-\n|{{flag|Laos}}||'''Most heavily bombed country in the world per capita''' \n| || align=\"right\" |Military||align=\"right\"| 2016\n|<ref>/https://www.cnn.com/2016/09/05/asia/united-states-laos-secret-war/</ref>\n|-\n|{{flag|Malawi}}||'''[[List of countries by GDP (nominal) per capita|Lowest GDP (nominal) per capita]]'''\n| || align=\"right\" |Economy||align=\"right\"|2014\n|\n|-\n|{{flag|Maldives}}||'''[[List of countries by highest point|Lowest highest point among all countries]]''', 2&nbsp;m (7&nbsp;ft)\n| || align=\"right\" |Geography ||align=\"right\"|2009\n|\n|-\n|{{flag|Mauritania}}||'''[[Global Slavery Index#Global Slavery Index 2014|Largest percentage of people in slavery]]''', 4%\n| || align=\"right\" |Demographics||align=\"right\"|2014\n|<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.globalslaveryindex.org/download|title=GSI 2014 Global Data and codebook|website=The Global Slavery Index|publisher=Walk Free Foundation|accessdate=12 January 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150120193727/http://www.globalslaveryindex.org/download/|archive-date=20 January 2015|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n<!--|-\n|{{flag|Mauritius}}||'''Most compact measured in [[Compactness measure of a shape|circular ratio]]''', 0.81425||align=\"right\"|Geography ||align=\"right\"|2009-->\n|-\n|{{flag|Federated States of Micronesia}}||'''[[List of countries by coast/area ratio|Highest coastline to area ratio]]''', 8,706.553 m/km\u00b2\n| || align=\"right\" |Geography ||align=\"right\"|2009\n|\n|-\n|{{flag|Mongolia}}||'''[[List of countries by population density|Least densely populated]]''', 1.92 per km\u00b2\n| || align=\"right\" |Demographics||align=\"right\"|2015\n|\n<!--|-\n|{{flag|Montenegro}}||'''[[List of countries by statehood|Youngest country]]''', established in 2006||align=\"right\"|History||align=\"right\"|2010-->\n|-\n|{{flag|Morocco}}||'''[[Phosphorus|Largest phosphorus reserve]]''', about 50 trillion metric tons of 67 trillion metric tons worldwide (about the 75% the world reserves)\n| || align=\"right\" |Industry||align=\"right\"|2011\n|\n|-\n|{{flag|Namibia}}||'''[[List of countries by income equality|Least equal income distribution]]'''\n| || align=\"right\" |Demographics <br /> Economy||align=\"right\"|2003\n|\n|-\n|{{flag|Nepal}}||'''[[List of countries by highest point|Highest elevation above the sea level]]''', 8,848 m (29,029&nbsp;ft) at [[Mount Everest]] (shared with [[China]])\n| || align=\"right\" |Geography ||align=\"right\"|2009\n|\n|-\n|{{flag|State of Palestine}}||'''[[List of countries by lowest point|Lowest depression below the sea level]]''', -428 m at [[Dead Sea]] (shared with [[Jordan]] and [[Israel]])\n| || align=\"right\" |Geography||align=\"right\"|2012\n|\n|-\n|{{flag|Panama}}||'''[[List of merchant marine capacity by country|Most merchant ships registered]]''', 6,323\n| || align=\"right\" |Transport||align=\"right\"|2008\n|\n|-\n|{{flag|Rwanda}}||'''[[Women in government#Women in national parliaments|Highest proportion of women in government]]''', 56.3%\n| || align=\"right\" |Politics||align=\"right\"|2013\n|\n|-\n|{{flag|San Marino}}||'''[[List of countries by vehicles per capita|Most motor vehicles per capita]]''', 1263 per 1000 population\n| || align=\"right\" |Transport <br /> Consumption||align=\"right\"|2010\n|\n|-\n|{{flag|Sierra Leone}}||'''[[List of countries by industrial production growth rate|Highest industrial production growth rate]]''', 88%\n| || align=\"right\" |Industry||align=\"right\"|2013\n|\n|-\n|{{flag|Sudan}}||'''Lowest level of innovation according to [[Global Innovation Index (Cornell University, INSEAD and WIPO)|Global Innovation Index]]''', score of 0.4\n| || align=\"right\" |Technology||align=\"right\"|2013\n|\n|-\n|{{flag|Suriname}}||'''[[List of countries by forest area|Highest percent of forest area]]''', 90.20%\n| || align=\"right\" |Geography ||align=\"right\"|2011\n|\n|-\n|{{flag|Ukraine}}||'''[[Sunflower seed#Cultivation|Largest sunflower seed producer]]''', output of 10.1 million metric tons\n| || align=\"right\" |Agriculture||align=\"right\"|2014\n|\n|-\n|{{flag|Uruguay}}||'''[[List of countries by northernmost point|Most southernmost northernmost point on land]]''', 30\u00b005'S\n| || align=\"right\" |Geography ||align=\"right\"|2009\n|\n|-\n|{{flag|Uzbekistan}}||'''[[Double landlocked#Doubly landlocked country|Largest double landlocked country]]''', 447,400&nbsp;km\u00b2 (172,742 sq mi)\n| || align=\"right\" |Geography||align=\"right\"|\n|\n|-\n|{{flag|Vietnam}}||'''[[List of countries by immigrant population|Smallest percentage of immigrant population]]''', 0.0249%\n| || align=\"right\" |Demographics||align=\"right\"|2005\n|\n|}\n\n==Countries without any entries==\nThe following fully recognized countries have no entries in the above list:\n\n{{Div col|colwidth=15em|rules=yes|gap=2em}}\n* {{flag|Algeria}}\n* {{flag|Angola}}\n* {{flag|Antigua and Barbuda}}\n* {{flag|Armenia}}\n* {{flag|Bahrain}}\n* {{flag|Barbados}}\n* {{flag|Belize}}\n* {{flag|Bolivia}}\n* {{flag|Bosnia and Herzegovina}}\n* {{flag|Burkina Faso}}\n* {{flag|Cape Verde}}\n* {{flag|Comoros}}\n* {{flag|Croatia}}\n* {{flag|Cyprus}}\n* {{flag|Dominica}}\n* {{flag|Dominican Republic}}\n* {{flag|Ecuador}}\n* {{flag|El Salvador}}\n* {{flag|Equatorial Guinea}}\n* {{flag|Gabon}}\n* {{flag|Georgia}}\n* {{flag|Ghana}}\n* {{flag|Grenada}}\n* {{flag|Guinea-Bissau}}\n* {{flag|Guyana}}\n* {{flag|Kiribati}}\n* {{flag|Kosovo}}\n* {{flag|Kyrgyzstan}}\n* {{flag|Latvia}}\n* {{flag|Liberia}}\n* {{flag|Lithuania}}\n* {{flag|Mali}}\n* {{flag|Malta}}\n* {{flag|Marshall Islands}}\n* {{flag|Mauritius}}\n* {{flag|Montenegro}}\n* {{flag|Mozambique}}\n* {{flag|Nauru}}\n* {{flag|Nicaragua}}\n* {{flag|North Macedonia}}\n* ''{{flag|Niue}}''\n* {{flag|Oman}}\n* {{flag|Palau}}\n* {{flag|Saint Kitts and Nevis}}\n* {{flag|Saint Lucia}}\n* {{flag|Saint Vincent and the Grenadines}}\n* {{flag|Samoa}}\n* {{flag|S\u00e3o Tom\u00e9 and Pr\u00edncipe}}\n* {{flag|Senegal}}\n* {{flag|Seychelles}}\n* {{flag|Slovakia}}\n* {{flag|Slovenia}}\n* {{flag|Solomon Islands}}\n* {{flag|Tajikistan}}\n* {{flag|Tanzania}}\n* {{flag|Togo}}\n* {{flag|Tonga}}\n* {{flag|Trinidad and Tobago}}\n* {{flag|Tunisia}}\n* {{flag|Turkmenistan}}\n* {{flag|Uganda}}\n* {{flag|Vanuatu}}\n* {{flag|Yemen}}\n* {{flag|Zambia}}\n* {{flag|Zimbabwe}}\n{{Div col end}}\n\n== See also ==\n* [[List of sovereign states]]\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.informationisbeautiful.net/visualizations/because-every-country-is-the-best-at-something/# Because Every Country Is The Best At Something]\n* [http://thedoghousediaries.com/5414 DOGHOUSE  |  What Each Country Leads The World In]\n\n{{Navboxes\n|list1 