c.ca/cccs/Publications/Commercial_Sexual_Exploitation_WWY_Manual.pdf Commercial sexual exploitation : creative ideas for working with children and youth. New Westminster, B.C. : Social Services and Community Safety Division, Justice Institute of B.C., 2002.]\n\n;Media\n* [http://www.walnet.org/csis/news/vancouver_97/westend-970731.html Pleasure and Pain: Inside the Sex Trade. The West Ender, July 31, 1997]\n* [https://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/british-columbia/decriminalize-sex-trade-vancouver-report-1.624534 Decriminalize sex trade: Vancouver report. CBC June 13, 2006]\n* Vancouver sex-trade laws blasted: 'Once the lights go out here, man, it's brutal. It's crazy. Globe and Mail June 14, 2006\n* [http://www.cbc.ca/canada/story/2006/05/19/woman-body.html Woman found dead near Edmonton linked to sex trade. CBC News, May 19, 2006]\n* [http://www.cbc.ca/canada/story/2006/05/17/alberta-kare.html New cases may be linked to Alberta sex-trade killings. CBC News May 17, 2006]\n* [http://www.cbc.ca/canada/story/2006/05/10/sextrade-murder.html Suspect in death of sex-trade worker has history of violence. CBC News,May 10, 2006.]\n\n;Analysis\n* [http://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/story/2012/03/26/f-vp-henry-prostitution.html Daniel Henry: How the court's views on prostitution have evolved: The world's oldest profession, Canada's latest answer. CBC March 27 2012]\n* [http://www.aidslex.org/site_documents/SX-0002E_1.pdf Not up to the challenge of change: An analysis of the report of the Subcommittee on Solicitation Laws. Canadian HIV/AIDS Legal Network Briefing Paper February 2007]\n\n;Other\n* [http://www2.hu-berlin.de/sexology/IES/canada.html Barrett M., et al. The International Encyclopedia of Sexuality: Canada.]\n* {{Cite news|title=Globalization & Migration |work=United Nations Platform for Action Committee: Women and the Economy |url=http://www.unpac.ca/economy/g_migration.html |accessdate= |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110514045035/http://www.unpac.ca/economy/g_migration.html |archivedate=May 14, 2011 |df= }}\n* [http://www.walnet.org/csis/papers/sdavis.html Sylvia Davis and Martha Shaffer. Prostitution in Canada: The Invisible Menace or the Menace of Invisibility? 1994]\n* [http://www.walnet.org/csis/reports/index.html Government Reports. Commercial Sex Information Service 2004]\n* [http://www.popcenter.org/problems/street_prostitution/PDFs/johnhow.pdf Prostitution. John Howard Society of Alberta 2001]\n{{Col-end}}\n{{refend}}\n\n{{North America topic|Prostitution in}}\n{{Prostitution in Canada}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Prostitution In Canada}}\n[[Category:Prostitution in Canada| ]]\n", "name_user": "Iridescent", "label": "safe", "comment": "Cleanup andtypo fixing,typo(s) fixed: \u2019s \u2192 's (2), 1991-5 \u2192 1991\u20135 (2)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Prostitution_in_Canada"}
{"title_page": "Albert Piette", "text_new": "{{Infobox person\n| name          = Albert Piette\n| image         = \n| alt           = \n| caption       = \n| birth_name    = \n| birth_date    = {{birth date and age|1960|4|18}}\n| birth_place   = [[Namur, Belgium|Namur]], [[Wallonia]], [[Belgium]]\n| nationality   = [[Belgian]]\n| occupation    = [[Professor]], [[author]]\n| years_active  = \n| known_for     = \n| notable_works = \n}}\n\n'''Albert Piette''' (born April 18, 1960 in [[Namur]], [[Belgium]]) is an [[anthropologist]] and a professor at the Department of Anthropology at [[Paris Nanterre University]].\n\nHis researches has first focused on the questions of [[observation]], especially in the religious world.<ref>See ''La religion de pr\u00e8s'' (M\u00e9taili\u00e9) and ''Le fait religieux'' (Economica) .</ref> He describes and analyses details and ordinary forms in situations of everyday life - what he named the minor mode of reality.<ref>''Le mode mineur de la r\u00e9alit\u00e9'' (Peeters)</ref>\n\nFor several years,<ref>This is visible starting with the book ''L'acte d'exister'' and in his next books.</ref> the objective of Albert Piette has been to elaborate [[anthropology]] as a specific discipline, a science of the human being, different from [[sociology]] and [[ethnology]], with precise theoretical and methodological orientations and themes. The aim is to let in the human being, as a specific entity, inside anthropology, which he considers focused on cultural sets or social systems, and also on situations, actions, relations.  In contrast, the task of existential anthropology would thus be to observe, describe and analyze the microcontinuity of the human being, living the moments and situations according to various modalities of presence-absence and passivity-activity. Albert Piette does not want to regard existential anthropology as secondary; on the contrary he considers it as crucial for anthropology, its future and its detachment from social sciences. In this project, he continues to make of the minor mode an essential element to define the anthropological difference.<ref>''Anthropologie existentiale'' (Petra) and ''L'origine de la croyance'' (Berg International)</ref>\n\nWith the aim of detailed observations of human beings, Albert Piette thinks that [[ethnography]], working especially on activities and groups, is less appropriate than phenomenography, which focuses on singular individuals. As the word implies, phenomenography studies on the one hand what appears, movements, postures, gestures, and on the other hand, as an empirical counterpoint to [[phenomenology]], it also attempts to describe states of mind and feelings in the continuity of moments.<ref>See in particular ''Contre le relationnisme'' (Le Bord de l'eau), ''What is Existential Anthropology?'' (Berghahn) and ''Existence in the Details'' (Duncker and Humblot)</ref>\n\nDeveloping this perspective, Albert Piette calls upon the notion of volume to clarity the focus of existential anthropology on the human being, which he calls a volume of being or a human volume.<ref>See ''Le volume humain'' (Le Bord de l'eau) and ''Theoretical Anthropology or How to Observe a Human Being'' (Wiley-Iste)</ref> This notion, associated to that of volumography and volumology, allows him to insist on the unity of the human entity, its entirety, its unicitiy and also its stylistic continuity.\n\n==Books==\n* ''Les Jeux de la f\u00eate'', Paris, Publications de la Sorbonne, 1988.\n* {{cite book|title=Le mode mineur de la r\u00e9alit\u00e9 : paradoxes et photographies en anthropologie|date=1992|publisher=Peeters|location=Louvain-la-Neuve|isbn=9789068314427}}\n* ''Les Religiosit\u00e9s s\u00e9culi\u00e8res'', Paris, [[PUF]], 1993.\n* {{cite book|title=Ethnographie de l'action : l'observation des d\u00e9tails|date=1996|publisher=Editions M\u00e9taili\u00e9|location=Paris|isbn=9782864242147}}\n* ''La Religion de pr\u00e8s. L'activit\u00e9 religieuse en train de se faire'', Paris, M\u00e9taili\u00e9, 1999.\n* {{cite book|title=D\u00e9tails d'amour ou le lien par l'\u00e9criture|date=2003|publisher=L'Harmattan|location=Paris|isbn=9782296312418}}\n* ''Le Fait religieux. Une th\u00e9orie de la religion ordinaire'', Paris, Economica, 2003.\n* {{cite book|title=Le temps du deuil : essai d'anthropologie existentielle|date=2005|publisher=Ed. de l'Atelier|location=Paris|isbn=9782708238312}}\n* ''Petit trait\u00e9 d'anthropologie'', Marchienne-au-Pont, Socrate Editions Promarex, 2006.\n* ''L'\u00catre humain, une question de d\u00e9tails'', Marchienne-au-Pont, Socrate Editions Promarex, 2007.\n* ''L'Acte d'exister. Une ph\u00e9nom\u00e9nographie de la pr\u00e9sence'', Marchienne-au-Pont, Socrate Editions Promarex, 2009. \n* ''Anthropologie existentiale'', Paris, P\u00e9tra, 2009.\n* ''Propositions anthropologiques pour refonder la discipline'', Paris, P\u00e9tra, 2010.\n* ''Fondements \u00e0 une anthropologie des hommes'', Paris, Hermann, 2011.\n* ''De l'ontologie en anthropologie'', Paris, Berg International, 2012.\n* ''L'origine de la croyance'', Paris, Berg International, 2013.\n* ''Contre le relationnisme. Lettre aux anthropologues'', Lormont, Le Bord de l'eau, 2014.\n* ''M\u00e9ditation pessoanienne. Science de l'existence et destin de l'Anthropologue'', Paris, \u00c9ditions Mat\u00e9riologiques, 2014.\n* ''Avec Heidegger contre Heidegger. Introduction \u00e0 une anthropologie de l'existence'', Lausanne, \u00c9ditions L'\u00c2ge d'Homme, 2014.\n* '' What is Existential Anthropology ?'', edited with [[Michael Jackson (anthropologist)|Michael Jackson]], New York - Oxford, [[Berghahn Books|Berghahn]], 2015. {{isbn|978-1-78238-636-0}}\n* '' Existence in the Details. Theory and Methodology in Existential Anthropology'', Berlin, Duncker & Humblot, 2015. {{isbn|9783428146772}} \n* ''Aristote, Heidegger, Pessoa : l'appel de l'anthropologie'', Paris, P\u00e9tra, 2016.\n* ''L'humain impens\u00e9'', Paris, Presses Universitaires de Paris Ouest (in collaboration with Jean-Michel Salanskis), 2016.\n* ''Antropologia dell'esistenza'', Venezia, Alvisopoli, 2016.\n* ''Separate Humans. Anthropology, Ontology, Existence'', Milan, Mimesis International, 2016.\n* '' Le volume humain. Esquisse d'une science de l'homme'', Lormont, Le Bord de l'eau, 2017. \n* '' Dictionnaire de l'humain'' (ed. with J.-M. Salanskis et al.), Nanterre, Presses Universitaires de Paris Nanterre, 2018.\n* ''Anthropologie th\u00e9orique ou comment regarder un \u00eatre humain'', London, Iste Editions, 2018 (translated in English: ''Theoretical Anthropology or How to Observe a Human Being'', Wiley-Iste, 2019).\n\n== Online articles and book chapters ==\nDirectly downloadable on [http://www.albertpiette.net/pages/textes-en-ligne/ Albert Piette's homepage] and on [https://u-paris10.academia.edu/AlbertPiette/ Academia.edu]\n\n== A few comments ==\n* Beno\u00eet Haug, Gwendoline Torterat, Isabelle Jabiot (\u00e9ds), ''Des instants et des jours. Observer et d\u00e9crire l\u2019existence'', Paris, P\u00e9tra, 2017.\n* Concetta Garofalo, L\u2019anthropologia esistenziale di Albert Piette. Ripartie dall\u2019individuo, ''Dialoghi Mediterranei'', 21, September 2016 (online).\n* Laurent Denizeau, L'infra de l'humain : Du mode mineur de la r\u00e9alit\u00e9 \u00e0 l'anthropologie existentiale dans l'oeuvre d'Albert Piette, ''Le Philosophoire'', 44, 2, 2015, pp. 177-199.\n* Catherine R\u00e9my and Laurent Denizeau (\u00e9ds), ''La Vie, mode mineur'', Paris, Presses des Mines, 2015.\n* Yann Schmitt, Refaire de l'anthropologie. Le singulier avant les relations, ''L'Homme'', 214, 2015/2, pp. 137-146.\n* Laurent Denizeau, Considering Human Existence: An Existential Reading of Michael Jackson and Albert Piette, in M. Jackson and A. Piette (eds), ''What is Existential Anthropology?'', New York-Oxford, Berghahn Books, 2015, pp. 214-236.\n* Stanislas Deprez, The Minor Mode. Albert Piette and the Reshaping of Anthropology, ''Sociologus'', Volume 64, Issue 1, 2014, pp. 87-96.\n* Fanny Colonna, Trois monoth\u00e9ismes, une cause commune, ''Th\u00e9oR\u00e8mes'' [Anthropologie des religions], February 2011 (online).\n* James A. Beckford, A Minimalist Sociology of Religion?, in J. A. Beckford et J. Walliss (eds), ''Theorising Religion: Classical and Contemporary Debates'', Aldershot, Ashgate Publishing, 2006, pp. 182-196.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Piette, Albert}}\n[[Category:Anthropologists of religion]]\n[[Category:French anthropologists]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:1960 births]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox person\n| name          = Albert Piette\n| image         = \n| alt           = \n| caption       = \n| birth_name    = \n| birth_date    = {{birth date and age|1960|4|18}}\n| birth_place   = [[Namur, Belgium|Namur]], [[Wallonia]], [[Belgium]]\n| nationality   = [[Belgian]]\n| occupation    = [[Professor]], [[author]]\n| years_active  = \n| known_for     = \n| notable_works = \n}}\n\n'''Albert Piette''' (born April 18, 1960 in [[Namur]], [[Belgium]]) is an [[anthropologist]] and a professor at the Department of Anthropology at [[Paris Nanterre University]].\n\nHis researches has first focused on the questions of [[observation]], especially in the religious world <ref> See ''La religion de pr\u00e8s'' (M\u00e9taili\u00e9) and ''Le fait religieux'' (Economica) .</ref>. He describes and analyses details and ordinary forms in situations of everyday life - what he named the minor mode of reality <ref> ''Le mode mineur de la r\u00e9alit\u00e9'' (Peeters) </ref>.\n\nFor several years <ref> This is visible starting with the book ''L'acte d'exister'' and in his next books.</ref>, the objective of Albert Piette has been to elaborate [[anthropology]] as a specific discipline, a science of the human being, different from [[sociology]] and [[ethnology]], with precise theoretical and methodological orientations and themes. The aim is to let in the human being, as a specific entity, inside anthropology, which he considers focused on cultural sets or social systems, and also on situations, actions, relations.  In contrast, the task of existential anthropology would thus be to observe, describe and analyze the microcontinuity of the human being, living the moments and situations according to various modalities of presence-absence and passivity-activity. Albert Piette does not want to regard existential anthropology as secondary; on the contrary he considers it as crucial for anthropology, its future and its detachment from social sciences. In this project, he continues to make of the minor mode an essential element to define the anthropological difference <ref> ''Anthropologie existentiale'' (Petra) and ''L'origine de la croyance'' (Berg International)</ref>.\n\nWith the aim of detailed observations of human beings, Albert Piette thinks that [[ethnography]], working especially on activities and groups, is less appropriate than phenomenography, which focuses on singular individuals. As the word implies, phenomenography studies on the one hand what appears, movements, postures, gestures, and on the other hand, as an empirical counterpoint to [[phenomenology]], it also attempts to describe states of mind and feelings in the continuity of moments <ref> See in particular ''Contre le relationnisme'' (Le Bord de l'eau), ''What is Existential Anthropology?'' (Berghahn) and ''Existence in the Details'' (Duncker and Humblot) </ref>. \n\nDeveloping this perspective, Albert Piette calls upon the notion of volume to clarity the focus of existential anthropology on the human being, which he calls a volume of being or a human volume <ref> See ''Le volume humain'' (Le Bord de l'eau) and ''Theoretical Anthropology or How to Observe a Human Being'' (Wiley-Iste) </ref>. This notion, associated to that of volumography and volumology, allows him to insist on the unity of the human entity, its entirety, its unicitiy and also its stylistic continuity. \n\n\n==Books==\n* ''Les Jeux de la f\u00eate'', Paris, Publications de la Sorbonne, 1988.\n* {{cite book|title=Le mode mineur de la r\u00e9alit\u00e9 : paradoxes et photographies en anthropologie|date=1992|publisher=Peeters|location=Louvain-la-Neuve|isbn=9789068314427}}\n* ''Les Religiosit\u00e9s s\u00e9culi\u00e8res'', Paris, [[PUF]], 1993.\n* {{cite book|title=Ethnographie de l'action : l'observation des d\u00e9tails|date=1996|publisher=Editions M\u00e9taili\u00e9|location=Paris|isbn=9782864242147}}\n* ''La Religion de pr\u00e8s. L'activit\u00e9 religieuse en train de se faire'', Paris, M\u00e9taili\u00e9, 1999.\n* {{cite book|title=D\u00e9tails d'amour ou le lien par l'\u00e9criture|date=2003|publisher=L'Harmattan|location=Paris|isbn=9782296312418}}\n* ''Le Fait religieux. Une th\u00e9orie de la religion ordinaire'', Paris, Economica, 2003.\n* {{cite book|title=Le temps du deuil : essai d'anthropologie existentielle|date=2005|publisher=Ed. de l'Atelier|location=Paris|isbn=9782708238312}}\n* ''Petit trait\u00e9 d'anthropologie'', Marchienne-au-Pont, Socrate Editions Promarex, 2006.\n* ''L'\u00catre humain, une question de d\u00e9tails'', Marchienne-au-Pont, Socrate Editions Promarex, 2007.\n* ''L'Acte d'exister. Une ph\u00e9nom\u00e9nographie de la pr\u00e9sence'', Marchienne-au-Pont, Socrate Editions Promarex, 2009. \n* ''Anthropologie existentiale'', Paris, P\u00e9tra, 2009.\n* ''Propositions anthropologiques pour refonder la discipline'', Paris, P\u00e9tra, 2010.\n* ''Fondements \u00e0 une anthropologie des hommes'', Paris, Hermann, 2011.\n* ''De l'ontologie en anthropologie'', Paris, Berg International, 2012.\n* ''L'origine de la croyance'', Paris, Berg International, 2013.\n* ''Contre le relationnisme. Lettre aux anthropologues'', Lormont, Le Bord de l'eau, 2014.\n* ''M\u00e9ditation pessoanienne. Science de l'existence et destin de l'Anthropologue'', Paris, \u00c9ditions Mat\u00e9riologiques, 2014.\n* ''Avec Heidegger contre Heidegger. Introduction \u00e0 une anthropologie de l'existence'', Lausanne, \u00c9ditions L'\u00c2ge d'Homme, 2014.\n* '' What is Existential Anthropology ?'', edited with [[Michael Jackson (anthropologist)|Michael Jackson]], New York - Oxford, [[Berghahn Books|Berghahn]], 2015. {{isbn|978-1-78238-636-0}}\n* '' Existence in the Details. Theory and Methodology in Existential Anthropology'', Berlin, Duncker & Humblot, 2015. {{isbn|9783428146772}} \n* ''Aristote, Heidegger, Pessoa : l'appel de l'anthropologie'', Paris, P\u00e9tra, 2016.\n* ''L'humain impens\u00e9'', Paris, Presses Universitaires de Paris Ouest (in collaboration with Jean-Michel Salanskis), 2016.\n* ''Antropologia dell'esistenza'', Venezia, Alvisopoli, 2016.\n* ''Separate Humans. Anthropology, Ontology, Existence'', Milan, Mimesis International, 2016.\n* '' Le volume humain. Esquisse d'une science de l'homme'', Lormont, Le Bord de l'eau, 2017. \n* '' Dictionnaire de l'humain'' (ed. with J.-M. Salanskis et al.), Nanterre, Presses Universitaires de Paris Nanterre, 2018.\n* ''Anthropologie th\u00e9orique ou comment regarder un \u00eatre humain'', London, Iste Editions, 2018 (translated in English: ''Theoretical Anthropology or How to Observe a Human Being'', Wiley-Iste, 2019). \n\n== Online articles and book chapters ==\nDirectly downloadable on [http://www.albertpiette.net/pages/textes-en-ligne/ Albert Piette's homepage] and on [https://u-paris10.academia.edu/AlbertPiette/ Academia.edu]\n\n== A few comments ==\n* Beno\u00eet Haug, Gwendoline Torterat, Isabelle Jabiot (\u00e9ds), ''Des instants et des jours. Observer et d\u00e9crire l\u2019existence'', Paris, P\u00e9tra, 2017.\n* Concetta Garofalo, L\u2019anthropologia esistenziale di Albert Piette. Ripartie dall\u2019individuo, ''Dialoghi Mediterranei'', 21, September 2016 (online).\n* Laurent Denizeau, L'infra de l'humain : Du mode mineur de la r\u00e9alit\u00e9 \u00e0 l'anthropologie existentiale dans l'oeuvre d'Albert Piette, ''Le Philosophoire'', 44, 2, 2015, pp. 177-199.\n* Catherine R\u00e9my and Laurent Denizeau (\u00e9ds),